    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<p>If you installed the License Server using the RenderMan Installer then you already have the pixar.license file you need in:</p><p><sup> /opt/pixar/pixar.license</sup></p><p>If you installed by downloading and running the .rpm then after the installation run the Pixar LicenseApp as a root users or with sudo, which is normally done this way:</p><p><sup> sudo /opt/pixar/PixarLicense-LA-23.0/LicenseApp/bin/LicenseApp</sup></p><p>This will help you download and install the license file for the license server. When LicenseApp discovers there is no license file on disk, it will look like:</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"600\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542212557/lin_licapp_nolicense.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=454&amp;height=430\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542212557/lin_licapp_nolicense.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"430\" data-width=\"454\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542212569\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"lin_licapp_nolicense.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542212557\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"533f4061-9e90-4672-a34f-5efa16d98050\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542212557/lin_licapp_nolicense.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=454&amp;height=430 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542212557/lin_licapp_nolicense.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=454&amp;height=430 1x\"></span><p>Click the &quot;Get License&quot; button to download a new license file for the license server. It will place this license file in:</p><p><sup>/opt/pixar/pixar.license</sup></p><p>If you do have a license, but the license server has not yet been started, RenderMan will report a license error:</p><div class=\"code panel pdl conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"6a248f4a-aeb5-468b-be06-0e9d90c12a9d\" data-macro-name=\"code\" style=\"border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"codeContent panelContent pdl\">\n<pre class=\"syntaxhighlighter-pre\" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=\"brush: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence\" data-theme=\"Confluence\">R50005 {SEVERE}  License error - code 111:  connect Connection refused\nR50005 {CONTINUED} license source: 9010@mylicserver</pre>\n</div></div><p>If you then run the LicenseApp, it will likewise report that it was not able to run contact the license server.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"600\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542212557/licenseAppServerDown.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=529&amp;height=521\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542212557/licenseAppServerDown.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"521\" data-width=\"529\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542212575\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"licenseAppServerDown.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542212557\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"f7579382-b6cc-40cb-95c0-b5385aa7a728\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542212557/licenseAppServerDown.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=529&amp;height=521 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542212557/licenseAppServerDown.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=529&amp;height=521 1x\"></span><p>The LicenseApp is a useful tool for indicating the current state of your license server, it can be run on the client machines as well and will remotely query the server for its status.</p><h3 id=\"LinuxLicenseServer-SettinguptheLicenseServiceonLinux\">Setting up the License Service on Linux</h3><p>Before the License Server can be started, it must be installed as a service on the Linux machine that the floating license is keyed to. To do this, execute the following command in a shell window:</p><div class=\"code panel pdl conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"2dac6575-b090-49d4-81ca-fc29c7124fc5\" data-macro-name=\"code\" style=\"border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"codeContent panelContent pdl\">\n<pre class=\"syntaxhighlighter-pre\" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=\"brush: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence\" data-theme=\"Confluence\">sudo bash /opt/pixar/PixarLicense-LA-23.0/linux_installService.sh</pre>\n</div></div><h3 id=\"LinuxLicenseServer-StartingtheLicenseServer\">Starting the License Server</h3><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-warning conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"deda4388-a32b-4e61-8f0b-51eed4e92263\" data-macro-name=\"warning\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-error confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><p>NOTE: You must setup the license service using the command outlined above to ensure that the service can be easily started, stopped, or restarted.</p></div></div><p /><p>To start the license service, execute the following command in a shell window:</p><div class=\"code panel pdl conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"89a75e99-83b5-4203-8f74-ef3812f3f52c\" data-macro-name=\"code\" style=\"border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"codeContent panelContent pdl\">\n<pre class=\"syntaxhighlighter-pre\" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=\"brush: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence\" data-theme=\"Confluence\">sudo service pixar-license start</pre>\n</div></div><p>When the License Server is running correctly, the LicenseApp program will display information about license features and the counts:</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"600\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542212557/lin_licapp_withlicense.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=454&amp;height=430\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542212557/lin_licapp_withlicense.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"430\" data-width=\"454\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542212572\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"lin_licapp_withlicense.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542212557\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"5f02e820-c2b2-440e-ac3d-830687db15d4\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542212557/lin_licapp_withlicense.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=454&amp;height=430 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542212557/lin_licapp_withlicense.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=454&amp;height=430 1x\"></span><p>RenderMan and other plugins should then run as expected.</p><h3 id=\"LinuxLicenseServer-StoppingtheLicenseServer\">Stopping the License Server</h3><p>If you need to stop the license service for some reason, execute the following command in a shell window:</p><div class=\"code panel pdl conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"3c806801-85d4-4236-b814-4c7826685841\" data-macro-name=\"code\" style=\"border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"codeContent panelContent pdl\">\n<pre class=\"syntaxhighlighter-pre\" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=\"brush: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence\" data-theme=\"Confluence\">sudo service pixar-license stop</pre>\n</div></div><p>When the License Server is no longer running, the LicenseApp program will display that information:</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"600\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542212557/licenseAppServerDown.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=529&amp;height=521\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542212557/licenseAppServerDown.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"521\" data-width=\"529\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542212575\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"licenseAppServerDown.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542212557\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"f7579382-b6cc-40cb-95c0-b5385aa7a728\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542212557/licenseAppServerDown.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=529&amp;height=521 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542212557/licenseAppServerDown.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=529&amp;height=521 1x\"></span><p>RenderMan and other plugins will no longer execute.</p><h3 id=\"LinuxLicenseServer-RestartingtheLicenseServer\">Restarting the License Server</h3><p>Every time you update your license file, you will then need to restart the license service to pick up the new license contents. The license can be restarted by typing the following into a shell:</p><div class=\"code panel pdl conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"7d055d2b-5781-4a6a-bed7-f34f00f9e3ef\" data-macro-name=\"code\" style=\"border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"codeContent panelContent pdl\">\n<pre class=\"syntaxhighlighter-pre\" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=\"brush: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence\" data-theme=\"Confluence\">sudo service pixarlicenseserver restart</pre>\n</div></div><p /><p>The license server is installed, by default, in /opt/pixar/PixarLicense-LA-&lt;version&gt; and contains the following components and scripts:</p><ol start=\"1\"><li><p /><ul><li><p><strong>PixarLicenseServer </strong>- the license server program</p></li><li><p><strong>LicenseApp/bin/LicenseApp </strong>- the license status application</p></li><li><p>queryPRMan.py - an example python script for querying the license server</p></li><li><p>linux_installService.sh - a script used by the installer to setup the license server system service</p></li></ul></li></ol><p>If you installed the License Server using the RenderMan Installer then you already have the pixar.license file you need in:</p><p><sup> /opt/pixar/pixar.license</sup></p><p>If you installed by downloading and running the .rpm then after the installation run the Pixar LicenseApp as a root users or with sudo, which is normally done this way:</p><p><sup> sudo /opt/pixar/PixarLicense-LA-23.0/LicenseApp/bin/LicenseApp</sup></p><p>This will help you download and install the license file for the license server. When LicenseApp discovers there is no license file on disk, it will look like:</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"600\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542212557/lin_licapp_nolicense.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=454&amp;height=430\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542212557/lin_licapp_nolicense.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"430\" data-width=\"454\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542212569\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"lin_licapp_nolicense.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542212557\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"533f4061-9e90-4672-a34f-5efa16d98050\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542212557/lin_licapp_nolicense.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=454&amp;height=430 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542212557/lin_licapp_nolicense.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=454&amp;height=430 1x\"></span><p>Click the &quot;Get License&quot; button to download a new license file for the license server. It will place this license file in:</p><p><sup>/opt/pixar/pixar.license</sup></p><p>If you do have a license, but the license server has not yet been started, RenderMan will report a license error:</p><div class=\"code panel pdl conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"7969eda5-262e-4e5f-97cb-1fb3a98cb8a7\" data-macro-name=\"code\" style=\"border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"codeContent panelContent pdl\">\n<pre class=\"syntaxhighlighter-pre\" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=\"brush: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence\" data-theme=\"Confluence\">R50005 {SEVERE}  License error - code 111:  connect Connection refused\nR50005 {CONTINUED} license source: 9010@mylicserver</pre>\n</div></div><p>If you then run the LicenseApp, it will likewise report that it was not able to run contact the license server.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"600\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542212557/licenseAppServerDown.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=529&amp;height=521\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542212557/licenseAppServerDown.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"521\" data-width=\"529\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542212575\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"licenseAppServerDown.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542212557\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"f7579382-b6cc-40cb-95c0-b5385aa7a728\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542212557/licenseAppServerDown.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=529&amp;height=521 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542212557/licenseAppServerDown.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=529&amp;height=521 1x\"></span><p>The LicenseApp is a useful tool for indicating the current state of your license server, it can be run on the client machines as well and will remotely query the server for its status.</p><h3 id=\"LinuxLicenseServer-SettinguptheLicenseServiceonLinux.1\">Setting up the License Service on Linux</h3><p>Before the License Server can be started, it must be installed as a service on the Linux machine that the floating license is keyed to. To do this, execute the following command in a shell window:</p><div class=\"code panel pdl conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"ed7e35a9-22e4-470c-987d-51fd00ec2896\" data-macro-name=\"code\" style=\"border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"codeContent panelContent pdl\">\n<pre class=\"syntaxhighlighter-pre\" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=\"brush: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence\" data-theme=\"Confluence\">sudo bash /opt/pixar/PixarLicense-LA-23.0/linux_installService.sh</pre>\n</div></div><h3 id=\"LinuxLicenseServer-StartingtheLicenseServer.1\">Starting the License Server</h3><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-warning conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"f9c6f347-5a47-41b8-ae6f-bcecf2ed591a\" data-macro-name=\"warning\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-error confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><p>NOTE: You must setup the license service using the command outlined above to ensure that the service can be easily started, stopped, or restarted.</p></div></div><p /><p>To start the license service, execute the following command in a shell window:</p><div class=\"code panel pdl conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"1d3024ac-c0bb-4ae1-9fa9-b8cdbb0b3600\" data-macro-name=\"code\" style=\"border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"codeContent panelContent pdl\">\n<pre class=\"syntaxhighlighter-pre\" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=\"brush: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence\" data-theme=\"Confluence\">sudo service pixar-license start</pre>\n</div></div><p>When the License Server is running correctly, the LicenseApp program will display information about license features and the counts:</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"600\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542212557/lin_licapp_withlicense.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=454&amp;height=430\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542212557/lin_licapp_withlicense.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"430\" data-width=\"454\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542212572\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"lin_licapp_withlicense.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542212557\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"5f02e820-c2b2-440e-ac3d-830687db15d4\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542212557/lin_licapp_withlicense.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=454&amp;height=430 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542212557/lin_licapp_withlicense.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=454&amp;height=430 1x\"></span><p>RenderMan and other plugins should then run as expected.</p><h3 id=\"LinuxLicenseServer-StoppingtheLicenseServer.1\">Stopping the License Server</h3><p>If you need to stop the license service for some reason, execute the following command in a shell window:</p><div class=\"code panel pdl conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"f5590832-afcb-457c-9a4e-fb49bf0c04fd\" data-macro-name=\"code\" style=\"border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"codeContent panelContent pdl\">\n<pre class=\"syntaxhighlighter-pre\" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=\"brush: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence\" data-theme=\"Confluence\">sudo service pixar-license stop</pre>\n</div></div><p>When the License Server is no longer running, the LicenseApp program will display that information:</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"600\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542212557/licenseAppServerDown.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=529&amp;height=521\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542212557/licenseAppServerDown.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"521\" data-width=\"529\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542212575\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"licenseAppServerDown.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542212557\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"f7579382-b6cc-40cb-95c0-b5385aa7a728\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542212557/licenseAppServerDown.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=529&amp;height=521 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542212557/licenseAppServerDown.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330455246&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=529&amp;height=521 1x\"></span><p>RenderMan and other plugins will no longer execute.</p><h3 id=\"LinuxLicenseServer-RestartingtheLicenseServer.1\">Restarting the License Server</h3><p>Every time you update your license file, you will then need to restart the license service to pick up the new license contents. The license can be restarted by typing the following into a shell:</p><div class=\"code panel pdl conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"627e746b-5fff-4e81-ace3-c7c68455b64f\" data-macro-name=\"code\" style=\"border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"codeContent panelContent pdl\">\n<pre class=\"syntaxhighlighter-pre\" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=\"brush: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence\" data-theme=\"Confluence\">sudo service pixarlicenseserver restart</pre>\n</div></div><p /><p>The license server is installed, by default, in /opt/pixar/PixarLicense-LA-&lt;version&gt; and contains the following components and scripts:</p><ol start=\"1\"><li><p /><ul><li><p><strong>PixarLicenseServer </strong>- the license server program</p></li><li><p><strong>LicenseApp/bin/LicenseApp </strong>- the license status application</p></li><li><p>queryPRMan.py - an example python script for querying the license server</p></li><li><p>linux_installService.sh - a script used by the installer to setup the license server system service</p></li></ul></li></ol>"
    }
  },
